{% extends "_base.html.j2" %}{% block content %}<main class="container"><h1>Sources and Methodology</h1><p class="lede">The UAP Index is a navigation layer over public records and source-labeled reports.</p><h2>Source Classes</h2><ul><li><strong>Official:</strong> AARO, NARA, NASA, Congress, Federal Register.</li><li><strong>FOIA archive:</strong> The Black Vault and similar document repositories.</li><li><strong>Research outlet:</strong> UAP-specific reporting and analysis.</li><li><strong>Witness database:</strong> public sighting reports such as NUFORC.</li><li><strong>News:</strong> Google News indexed coverage.</li></ul><h2>Important Limitation</h2><p>A record, claim, or mention is not proof beyond the cited source. The site labels confidence and unresolved gaps so readers can inspect the evidence trail themselves.</p></main>{% endblock %}